  2. Click the ⚙️ “Settings” tab (top right, not inside a “Pages” app)

  3. In the left sidebar, scroll and click “Pages” under the “Code and automation” section (not “Plan” or “Billing”)

    • You may also need to scroll far down in the main settings tab

  4. You’ll see a section titled “GitHub Pages” or “Build and Deployment”

  5. Under “Source”, select:

    • Branch: main

    • Folder: / (root)

  6. Click Save

✅ After 30–60 seconds, GitHub should show a green banner with:

csharp
Your site is published at https://yourusername.github.io/repository-name/

If You Still Don’t See It:

Double-check that:

  • You’re in the actual repository Settings, not your account or plan settings

  • You uploaded the files to the correct repository

  • Your repo is Public
